    "The proactive engagement of diverse stakeholder groups in the AI development process can provide valuable insights into the multifaceted impacts of technology on different communities.",
    "Additionally, the results advocate for the establishment of ethical oversight mechanisms, such as review boards and ethics committees, to evaluate AI projects for potential biases and fairness issues.",
    "The ongoing dialogue between AI developers, ethicists, policymakers, and the public is crucial for navigating the ethical landscape of AI.",
    "Ultimately, the ethical implications of LLMs call for a concerted effort to align AI technologies with societal values and human rights, ensuring that the benefits of AI are shared broadly and equitably.",
